  "prompt": "How early can you check in at the airport for international flight?",
  "response": "For international flights, check-in typically opens about three hours before departure and closes about an hour before departure. However, these times can vary depending on the airline and the airport, so it's always a good idea to check with your specific airline for their recommendation. Some airports may allow you to check in earlier, especially if they are busy, while others may have more rigid schedules. Additionally, many airlines allow online check-in up to 24 hours before departure, which can save you time at the airport.",
